00:23:07,586 --> 00:23:09,122
You play chess together,

486
00:23:09,187 --> 00:23:11,098
you're the one who asked
him to invest the pension.

487
00:23:12,023 --> 00:23:14,503
I get his mail,
I open his car door,

488
00:23:14,559 --> 00:23:16,630
I buy his cheese.
We're not friends.

489
00:23:16,962 --> 00:23:18,339
Let me ask you something,
Kovaks.

490
00:23:18,397 --> 00:23:20,604
If he's innocent,
where's the money?

491
00:23:20,665 --> 00:23:21,735
How should I know?

492
00:23:22,501 --> 00:23:25,675
The same way you knew
I was from Forest Hills.

493
00:23:25,737 --> 00:23:27,011
You pay attention.

494
00:23:30,876 --> 00:23:33,015
I just want to know what I'm
supposed to tell my staff.

495
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:36,257
Is that too much to ask?

496
00:23:37,349 --> 00:23:39,192
Tell them he's guilty.

497
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:42,528
Get on the car!

498
00:23:42,587 --> 00:23:43,964
Hey! Hey, hey!

499
00:23:44,022 --> 00:23:45,968
Come on, put
your hands behind your back!

500
00:23:46,024 --> 00:23:47,435
Come on, man,
what's this about?

501
00:23:47,492 --> 00:23:49,438
This is bullshit! Shit!
That's police brutality, yo!

502
00:23:49,694 --> 00:23:51,037
Come on now.

503
00:23:51,096 --> 00:23:52,541
Man in the suit,
you seeing this shit?

504
00:23:52,597 --> 00:23:54,099
You're my witness.
Take a cell phone picture.

505
00:23:54,166 --> 00:23:55,645
Take a picture, man.

506
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:57,373
No, my cell phone
doesn't have a camera.

507
00:23:57,702 --> 00:23:59,875
If you see Rita, tell her I
said to call her brother.

508
00:23:59,938 --> 00:24:01,645
Rita? Yeah, her brother's
a bail bondsman.

509
00:24:01,706 --> 00:24:02,810
Tell her I said
to use that money

510
00:24:02,874 --> 00:24:04,512
I gave her to get
her teeth fixed.

511
00:24:04,576 --> 00:24:06,453
Come on now, what you got
to be pushing me like that?

512
00:24:12,951 --> 00:24:17,195
<i>Ladies and
gentlemen, the next Brooklyn bound</i>

513
00:24:17,255 --> 00:24:20,099
<i>local train is now arriving.</i>

514
00:24:20,158 --> 00:24:22,900
<i>Please step away
from the platform edge,</i>

515
00:24:22,961 --> 00:24:27,341
<i>especially when trains are
entering and leaving the station.</i>

516
00:24:47,185 --> 00:24:48,459
Hello.

517
00:24:49,488 --> 00:24:51,798
<i>Dr. Carr, dial 118, please.</i>

518
00:24:54,593 --> 00:24:56,539
Hey, what happened?

519
00:24:56,595 --> 00:24:58,768
Lester tried to step in front
of a subway train tonight.

520
00:24:59,364 --> 00:25:01,640
An off-duty
traffic cop was there

521
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:03,304
and pulled him back
at the last second.

522
00:25:03,368 --> 00:25:05,211
They have him on
a 48-hour hold.

523
00:25:05,270 --> 00:25:06,305
Where is he?

524
00:25:20,619 --> 00:25:22,963
If you wanted a sick day,
all you had to do was ask.

525
00:25:24,756 --> 00:25:26,133
Seriously, I need
you back at work.

526
00:25:26,958 --> 00:25:28,767
I'm going to tell the
doctor somebody pushed you.

527
00:25:28,827 --> 00:25:30,500
It was a misunderstanding,
okay?

528
00:25:32,497 --> 00:25:34,602
I gave it to him, Josh.
All my money.

529
00:25:34,666 --> 00:25:36,703
I asked him to
invest it for me.

530
00:25:37,702 --> 00:25:38,976
Shaw?
Yeah.

531
00:25:39,237 --> 00:25:43,242
A couple of months ago, I gave him
everything I had, my life savings.

532
00:25:43,308 --> 00:25:44,810
Six years working the back door

533
00:25:44,876 --> 00:25:46,947
at the Waldorf,
nine at the Carlyle,

534
00:25:47,012 --> 00:25:49,618
three at the Pierre,
11 with you at The Tower.

535
00:25:50,482 --> 00:25:52,860
That's 29 years
of opening doors.

536
00:25:52,918 --> 00:25:56,365
$73,000 and change,
and I gave him every penny.

537
00:25:57,355 --> 00:26:00,063
In a few months I won't
have money for rent.

538
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:02,561
I can't retire now.

539
00:26:03,261 --> 00:26:07,334
All those years of opening
doors, year after year.

540
00:26:09,768 --> 00:26:12,977
Truth is, people can
open their own doors.

541
00:26:15,407 --> 00:26:16,909
Not the way you do it.

542
00:26:19,077 --> 00:26:22,183
Lester, he's going to pay
you back every penny.

543
00:26:23,081 --> 00:26:24,355
I promise.

544
00:26:26,751 --> 00:26:28,628
Josh, please calm down.

545
00:26:28,687 --> 00:26:29,688
Hold the elevator.

546
00:26:29,754 --> 00:26:31,324
You can't go up there.

547
00:26:31,489 --> 00:26:33,093
You're acting like a vigilante.
Move your hand.

548
00:26:33,158 --> 00:26:34,398
I won't move my hand.
Move your hand!

549
00:26:34,459 --> 00:26:35,870
Relax. You're not
using your head.

550
00:26:35,927 --> 00:26:37,304
Hey, Charlie.
Hey, Josh.

551
00:26:37,362 --> 00:26:38,432
Hey.

552
00:26:38,496 --> 00:26:40,635
So, they're evicting
me this morning.

553
00:26:40,699 --> 00:26:42,701
My wife already took the
kids, wants a divorce.

554
00:26:42,767 --> 00:26:44,474
So, if you need me,
I'll be living in this box.

555
00:26:44,536 --> 00:26:46,948
Can I ask you a question?
You're a Wall Street guy.

556
00:26:47,005 --> 00:26:48,746
When did Shaw realize
that it was over for him?

557
00:26:49,841 --> 00:26:51,650
Ten months, maybe a year.

558
00:26:51,710 --> 00:26:53,951
I heard he was interviewing
lawyers over the summer.

559
00:26:54,312 --> 00:26:56,314
So if he took someone's
money a few months ago?

560
00:26:56,715 --> 00:26:59,025
Probably needed the cash
to keep up appearances.

561
00:26:59,517 --> 00:27:02,589
Throw his famous Labor
Day party at the beach.

562
00:27:02,654 --> 00:27:05,100
At a certain point, it isn't
about securities fraud,

563
00:27:05,156 --> 00:27:06,191
it's about catering.

564
00:27:11,129 --> 00:27:12,904
Drop Mr. Fitzhugh on 59.

565
00:27:12,964 --> 00:27:14,204
I'm going to the penthouse.

566
00:27:14,699 --> 00:27:16,337
Wow! This is
going to be good.

567
00:27:19,237 --> 00:27:21,239
Don't get up. Whoa!
Where do you think you're going?

568
00:27:21,306 --> 00:27:22,979
We're just going
to get the trash.

569
00:27:23,041 --> 00:27:24,918
And the breakfast order.

570
00:27:24,976 --> 00:27:26,250
Go ahead.

571
00:27:28,647 --> 00:27:30,149
Takes a village.

572
00:27:35,020 --> 00:27:38,490
Good morning, Josh, Charlie, Enrique.
How are you doing?

573
00:27:38,556 --> 00:27:40,729
How was your Labor Day
party this year, Mr. Shaw?

574
00:27:40,792 --> 00:27:43,363
Must have been something, huh?
What did you serve? Crab legs?

575
00:27:43,428 --> 00:27:44,907
Surf and turf?

576
00:27:44,963 --> 00:27:48,206
I've always tried to extend
you a certain courtesy,

577
00:27:48,266 --> 00:27:49,768
but this tone you're using...

578
00:27:49,834 --> 00:27:51,905
What tone? Who gives
a shit about my tone?

579
00:27:52,637 --> 00:27:54,207
What are you, some
kind of tone master?

580
00:27:54,939 --> 00:27:56,885
Josh, come on.
I'm going to ask you one time, okay?

581
00:27:56,941 --> 00:27:58,750
So you better
think really hard.

582
00:27:58,810 --> 00:28:00,380
Why did you take
Lester's money?

583
00:28:04,916 --> 00:28:09,387
He came to me, he asked me to
invest and I did. It was a favor.

584
00:28:09,521 --> 00:28:13,094
Mm-hmm. $73,000? A favor?
Everything he had.

585
00:28:13,158 --> 00:28:14,899
Did Lester ask you
to come up here?

586
00:28:14,959 --> 00:28:16,233
Mr. Shaw,

587
00:28:16,294 --> 00:28:18,934
a few hours ago, Lester stepped
in front of a subway train.

588
00:28:19,931 --> 00:28:21,103
Oh, Jesus.

589
00:28:23,601 --> 00:28:25,945
Here we go.
What are you doing?

590
00:28:26,938 --> 00:28:29,544
Josh, you need to listen to me.
The FBI is lying to you.

591
00:28:29,607 --> 00:28:30,642
Josh, put down the club.

592
00:28:31,342 --> 00:28:33,447
Christ's sake, don't do
anything you can't undo.

593
00:28:35,046 --> 00:28:38,050
Investing money is a gamble.
It doesn't always pay off.

594
00:28:38,717 --> 00:28:40,060
Mr. Shaw, do you care?

595
00:28:40,118 --> 00:28:41,461
Josh, come on.
No, really.

596
00:28:41,519 --> 00:28:43,897
Do you feel any responsibility
for what happened to Lester?

597
00:28:44,189 --> 00:28:45,190
Of course I feel badly.

598
00:28:45,256 --> 00:28:47,827
I had no idea he was going
to lose everything.

599
00:28:47,892 --> 00:28:50,270
Lester has been a part of
my life for over a decade.

600
00:28:52,163 --> 00:28:55,201
Then why haven't you asked me
whether he's alive or dead?

601
00:28:58,303 --> 00:29:00,078
Josh, this car
is irreplaceable!

602
00:29:00,138 --> 00:29:01,776
Not like doormen!

603
00:29:02,173 --> 00:29:04,312
They make new ones
of those all the time.

604
00:29:04,375 --> 00:29:07,788
Must be 50 new doormen coming off
the line in Michigan right now!

605
00:29:08,379 --> 00:29:09,687
God damn it! Stop it!

606
00:29:09,748 --> 00:29:11,557
Want some Brie with your burger?
Here you go.

607
00:29:12,050 --> 00:29:13,120
Josh, don't!
Shh!

608
00:29:13,184 --> 00:29:14,959
Want me to come
work for you, huh?

609
00:29:15,019 --> 00:29:16,430
Want to steal me away
to Saint Bart's?

610
00:29:16,688 --> 00:29:19,032
Come on, let's go!
I'm ready to rock!

611
00:29:19,357 --> 00:29:21,359
Mr. Kovaks, let me have
a swing at that shit!

612
00:29:21,426 --> 00:29:23,963
No! Nobody touches
this car but me.

613
00:29:24,529 --> 00:29:27,305
You think Steve McQueen is the
coolest cat that ever lived?

614
00:29:27,599 --> 00:29:30,478
Guess what? Today, Steve
McQueen is my little bitch.

615
00:29:34,472 --> 00:29:35,542
Ooh!

616
00:29:36,307 --> 00:29:37,342
Ah!

617
00:29:37,976 --> 00:29:38,977
Oh!

618
00:29:40,011 --> 00:29:41,422
Whoops.

619
00:29:44,916 --> 00:29:48,193
Don't worry, I'll have the
help come clean that up.

620
00:29:49,254 --> 00:29:50,358
Let's go.

621
00:29:50,889 --> 00:29:53,529
Josh, aren't you
forgetting something?

622
00:29:54,592 --> 00:29:56,196
My breakfast order.

623
00:30:01,533 --> 00:30:02,910
Do you understand
the shit-storm

624
00:30:02,967 --> 00:30:04,241
that can be brought
down on this building?

625
00:30:04,302 --> 00:30:07,181
Shaw's lawyer will shove harassment,
destruction of property

626
00:30:07,238 --> 00:30:09,616
and civil rights charges
right down our throats!

627
00:30:09,674 --> 00:30:11,176
Now, I don't care what Shaw did

628
00:30:11,242 --> 00:30:12,983
or how much money
he's accused of stealing.

629
00:30:13,044 --> 00:30:15,388
And you know damn well I got
murdered by that son of a bitch!

630
00:30:15,446 --> 00:30:17,790
But a line has been crossed,
and a gang of vigilantes

631
00:30:17,849 --> 00:30:19,522
will not be tolerated
at The Tower.

632
00:30:19,584 --> 00:30:20,688
You're all fired.

633
00:30:21,119 --> 00:30:23,360
Hey, wait, hold on.
Mr. Simon, they had nothing to do with this.

634
00:30:23,421 --> 00:30:24,559
They just followed me up there.

635
00:30:24,622 --> 00:30:25,623
I don't give a shit!

636
00:30:25,690 --> 00:30:27,567
Mr. Simon, wait a minute, my
wife is eight months pregnant.

637
00:30:27,625 --> 00:30:29,798
You should have thought of that
before you walked in that apartment.

638
00:30:29,861 --> 00:30:31,033
We went up there for Lester!

639
00:30:31,095 --> 00:30:32,870
Lester's job is waiting
for him when he gets out.

640
00:30:32,931 --> 00:30:36,003
Meanwhile, the rest of you, I want
you out of the building right now.

641
00:30:54,919 --> 00:30:59,891
Um, the carpet cleaners are coming
tomorrow, they start on 44. Okay?

642
00:30:59,958 --> 00:31:01,403
Bye, Joshie.

643
00:31:01,926 --> 00:31:03,997
Good luck with the bar.

644
00:31:04,062 --> 00:31:06,736
I don't know what
you're talking about.

645
00:31:11,769 --> 00:31:15,546
All right. Let's go, everyone.
Back to work, okay?

646
00:31:21,913 --> 00:31:23,620
Hey, Charlie, wait!

647
00:31:23,681 --> 00:31:25,354
Wait. I'll call Sasha,
all right.

648
00:31:25,416 --> 00:31:26,451
I'll tell her you
tried to stop me.

649
00:31:26,517 --> 00:31:28,690
Please, don't do me any favors.

650
00:31:28,753 --> 00:31:30,198
And, Josh,
don't pretend to care now,

651
00:31:30,255 --> 00:31:31,893
I know you always
wanted to fire me.

652
00:31:32,690 --> 00:31:34,363
That's because you
stink at this job.

653
00:31:34,626 --> 00:31:37,004
So I stink? I stink?
Yeah.

654
00:31:37,061 --> 00:31:39,507
The guy who made Mrs. Jin
smile on Chinese New Year?

655
00:31:39,931 --> 00:31:41,467
Mrs. Jin is Korean.

656
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:42,901
She's what?

657
00:31:42,967 --> 00:31:44,037
That's why she was smiling.

658
00:31:44,102 --> 00:31:45,638
She's not Chinese,
she's Korean.

659
00:31:46,070 --> 00:31:47,447
And you believed her?

660
00:31:47,505 --> 00:31:49,246
Yeah, she's Korean.

661
00:31:50,308 --> 00:31:52,481
All right, Josh,
maybe she's Korean.

662
00:31:52,844 --> 00:31:54,323
Why are you whispering?
She is Korean.

663
00:31:54,379 --> 00:31:56,825
What's important is that she
appreciated the gesture I made,

664
00:31:56,881 --> 00:31:58,918
and that's more than I
can say for some people.

665
00:31:59,851 --> 00:32:01,831
Thanks for getting me fired.

666
00:32:29,047 --> 00:32:30,048
Hey.

667
00:32:30,114 --> 00:32:31,525
Hey. Thank you
for coming down.

668
00:32:31,582 --> 00:32:34,188
Yeah, no problem.
You got something for me?

669
00:32:34,252 --> 00:32:37,461
Yeah. I probably shouldn't
even be doing this,

670
00:32:37,522 --> 00:32:39,195
because it violates
everything I believe in,

671
00:32:39,257 --> 00:32:41,601
but I have to get my
employees' money back, so...

672
00:32:41,659 --> 00:32:44,299
This is Shaw's travel schedule
for the last 10 years.

673
00:32:44,362 --> 00:32:46,899
It's his guest registry.
Names of judges, politicians,

674
00:32:46,965 --> 00:32:48,911
women,
tail number of his plane,

675
00:32:48,967 --> 00:32:50,708
hull identification
number of his yacht,

676
00:32:50,768 --> 00:32:52,543
names of his race horses
in West Virginia...

677
00:32:52,603 --> 00:32:53,877
Gill's Pride and Sunny Day.

678
00:32:54,272 --> 00:32:56,274
Yeah, we have all that, Kovaks.

679
00:32:57,375 --> 00:32:59,548
And eventually they're gonna
sell his planes and his yachts,

680
00:32:59,610 --> 00:33:02,523
and his horses, and the bank
is going to take it all.

681
00:33:02,580 --> 00:33:04,184
You guys were his
smallest account.

682
00:33:05,516 --> 00:33:06,927
I'm sorry.

683
00:33:08,086 --> 00:33:09,588
It's okay.

684
00:33:11,789 --> 00:33:13,097
Thought I'd give it a shot.

685
00:33:15,660 --> 00:33:16,866
Kovaks,

686
00:33:17,762 --> 00:33:19,537
you wanna get drunk?

687
00:33:22,900 --> 00:33:23,935
Thanks.

688
00:33:24,002 --> 00:33:26,482
I've got to be
honest with you, Kovaks.

689
00:33:26,537 --> 00:33:30,280
The last time I drank this much at
a bar I made out with a fireman.

690
00:33:30,341 --> 00:33:32,514
Really?
How long ago was that?

691
00:33:33,011 --> 00:33:34,251
Tuesday.

692
00:33:35,446 --> 00:33:37,619
You know, you surprise me.

693
00:33:37,849 --> 00:33:42,127
I saw the security tape of you
beating the shit out of Shaw's car.

694
00:33:42,186 --> 00:33:43,688
That was badass.

695
00:33:44,722 --> 00:33:47,464
Yeah, well,
badass is my middle name.

696
00:33:47,525 --> 00:33:49,835
Nope. Your middle
name is Marvin.

697
00:33:49,894 --> 00:33:52,374
I know that from
your file. Marvin.

698
00:33:54,332 --> 00:33:55,436
All right.

699
00:33:55,900 --> 00:33:58,471
That's my dead grandfather
you're laughing at.

700
00:33:59,103 --> 00:34:00,275
What else is in my file?

701
00:34:00,671 --> 00:34:01,706
Oh.

702
00:34:01,773 --> 00:34:04,413
I know the year your
parents got divorced.

703
00:34:04,475 --> 00:34:06,352
Your SAT scores.

704
00:34:06,944 --> 00:34:08,048
You don't know my SAT scores.

705
00:34:08,112 --> 00:34:09,921
540, math.
480, verbal.

706
00:34:11,449 --> 00:34:13,292
I retook those.
Your scores went down

707
00:34:17,188 --> 00:34:19,395
I have to tell you something,

708
00:34:19,957 --> 00:34:21,903
and I really shouldn't
be telling you this,

709
00:34:21,959 --> 00:34:24,872
because it violates
everything I believe in.

710
00:34:24,929 --> 00:34:26,408
Mmm-hmm.

711
00:34:26,464 --> 00:34:28,967
We still haven't
found Shaw's safety net.

712
00:34:29,033 --> 00:34:33,778
All these guys, they keep some cash
close by in case they have to run.

713
00:34:33,838 --> 00:34:36,409
Shaw clears out all of his
accounts three months ago,

714
00:34:36,474 --> 00:34:38,511
20 million and change.

715
00:34:38,576 --> 00:34:40,749
But when we bust him,
the money isn't on him.

716
00:34:40,945 --> 00:34:42,117
Wait.

717
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:44,223
$20 million?

718
00:34:44,482 --> 00:34:47,429
There's a chance we'll
get lucky and find it.

719
00:34:48,653 --> 00:34:51,634
And if we get lucky,
maybe you can get lucky.

720
00:34:54,759 --> 00:34:56,170
I'm not lucky.

721
00:34:56,227 --> 00:34:58,400
You just have to be patient.

722
00:34:59,230 --> 00:35:01,870
I don't really have
time to be patient.

723
00:35:01,933 --> 00:35:03,913
Well, if you're
tired of waiting around,

724
00:35:03,968 --> 00:35:06,141
you can always try
the old-school approach.

725
00:35:06,304 --> 00:35:07,339
What's that?

726
00:35:08,539 --> 00:35:12,282
Grab some pitchforks and a couple
of guys and storm the castle.

727
00:35:12,343 --> 00:35:14,482
They'd never see you coming.

728
00:35:15,079 --> 00:35:16,615
I have to pee.

729
00:35:17,682 --> 00:35:19,719
Ooh! I'm gonna...
I have to go.

730
00:35:19,784 --> 00:35:21,127
Whoa, whoa.
