01:28:58,921 --> 01:29:00,764
<i>Lester,
you still there?</i>

1695
01:29:00,990 --> 01:29:03,436
Yeah, I'm here.
I'm holding four cabs at the north door.

1696
01:29:03,526 --> 01:29:04,596
Slight change of plan.

1697
01:29:04,661 --> 01:29:07,699
There's a white truck parked on 60th
and Broadway, keys on the visor.

1698
01:29:07,964 --> 01:29:08,999
<i>You got to back it
up to the elevator.</i>

1699
01:29:09,065 --> 01:29:10,066
I'm on my way.

1700
01:29:28,151 --> 01:29:31,530
Mr. Shaw, tell me
about this safe.

1701
01:29:31,654 --> 01:29:32,792
It's empty...

1702
01:29:32,855 --> 01:29:35,301
Doesn't matter if
it's empty or full.

1703
01:29:35,358 --> 01:29:36,837
A hidden safe
was never mentioned

1704
01:29:36,893 --> 01:29:38,770
in the inventory
of your apartment.

1705
01:29:38,828 --> 01:29:40,239
You neglected to inform us,

1706
01:29:40,296 --> 01:29:42,367
which is a violation of
your parole, therefore...

1707
01:29:42,432 --> 01:29:44,343
Where is my car?
Where is my goddamn car?

1708
01:29:44,400 --> 01:29:48,610
I hereby remand you to federal
custody until your real court date.

1709
01:29:48,671 --> 01:29:50,548
You just forfeited $10 million.

1710
01:29:50,606 --> 01:29:52,586
You think I care
about $10 million?

1711
01:29:52,642 --> 01:29:54,883
You think I care if I spend
a few nights in jail?

1712
01:29:54,944 --> 01:29:56,787
We both know I'm going to
be out by the weekend.

1713
01:29:56,846 --> 01:29:58,917
But you let that car
leave this building

1714
01:29:58,981 --> 01:30:01,291
and I promise you
won't get off so easy.

1715
01:30:01,951 --> 01:30:03,828
Take him away.
Lock it down.

1716
01:30:04,654 --> 01:30:06,759
This is Agent Huggins.
Lock down the building.

1717
01:30:16,833 --> 01:30:18,506
Show me the garage.

1718
01:30:18,568 --> 01:30:20,411
Okay. Yes, ma'am.

1719
01:30:23,272 --> 01:30:25,513
They got the car.
Come on! Come on!

1720
01:30:41,557 --> 01:30:43,230
There they are!

1721
01:30:43,292 --> 01:30:44,737
Here we go, baby.

1722
01:30:50,833 --> 01:30:52,073
Move out of the way.

1723
01:30:54,070 --> 01:30:55,276
Go. Go.

1724
01:31:03,412 --> 01:31:05,153
Get out of the way!

1725
01:31:10,720 --> 01:31:13,132
Careful. Careful.
Jesus Christ!

1726
01:31:19,595 --> 01:31:21,666
Freeze! Do not move!

1727
01:31:23,833 --> 01:31:25,107
Open it.

1728
01:31:32,008 --> 01:31:34,511
Son of a bitch!
It's a diversion.

1729
01:31:39,982 --> 01:31:42,428
Lester, they are gonna get hurt.
There is no way out of this.

1730
01:31:43,085 --> 01:31:44,689
I don't know what
you are talking about.

1731
01:31:44,754 --> 01:31:47,963
All I did is steal a truck
and try to commit suicide

1732
01:32:00,570 --> 01:32:02,948
Mr. Fitzhugh? FBI.
You're under arrest, sir.

1733
01:32:03,039 --> 01:32:04,040
Oh.

1734
01:32:04,140 --> 01:32:06,848
Please put your hands
behind your back.

1735
01:32:07,710 --> 01:32:11,021
Miss Montero,
FBI, you're under arrest.

1736
01:32:12,815 --> 01:32:15,523
Charlie Gibbs, FBI,
you're under arrest.

1737
01:32:15,585 --> 01:32:16,928
You have the right
to remain silent.

1738
01:32:16,986 --> 01:32:18,465
Anything you say,
can and will be

1739
01:32:18,521 --> 01:32:20,296
used against you
in a court of law.

1740
01:32:20,356 --> 01:32:21,801
You have the right
to an attorney.

1741
01:32:23,359 --> 01:32:27,899
Mr. Dev'Reaux, FBI. Show me your hands.
You're under arrest.

1742
01:32:38,674 --> 01:32:40,676
Show me your hands, Josh.

1743
01:32:43,779 --> 01:32:45,383
It was smart.

1744
01:32:45,915 --> 01:32:49,727
Thanksgiving, the parade,
changing the court date,

1745
01:32:50,386 --> 01:32:53,367
using Lester as a
diversion, lying to me.

1746
01:32:54,657 --> 01:32:57,433
We have reservations Saturday night
at six different restaurants.

1747
01:32:57,493 --> 01:33:00,406
I'll give you the names
if you wanna check.

1748
01:33:00,796 --> 01:33:03,242
That's okay, I trust you.

1749
01:33:29,191 --> 01:33:30,397
Where is my car?

1750
01:33:32,929 --> 01:33:34,738
Do you mean
the car made of gold?

1751
01:33:34,797 --> 01:33:37,676
Gold melted down
from the money you stole?

1752
01:33:37,733 --> 01:33:38,803
I haven't seen it.

1753
01:33:39,268 --> 01:33:40,872
They'll find it.

1754
01:33:41,270 --> 01:33:44,410
And when they do, my friends on the
bench will take no pity on you.

1755
01:33:44,707 --> 01:33:47,017
They'll make sure you go
away for a very long time.

1756
01:33:47,643 --> 01:33:49,384
See, you people
are working stiffs,

1757
01:33:49,712 --> 01:33:51,123
clock punchers.

1758
01:33:51,180 --> 01:33:52,921
Easily replaced and erased.

1759
01:33:53,549 --> 01:33:55,586
And just know that while you
are all sitting in jail,

1760
01:33:55,952 --> 01:33:57,431
I'll be right up
there in the penthouse

1761
01:33:57,486 --> 01:33:59,625
of The Tower,
doing what I do best.

1762
01:34:00,323 --> 01:34:02,064
We may be going to
jail for a few years,

1763
01:34:02,124 --> 01:34:05,503
but you, you're going
for the rest of your life.

1764
01:34:06,095 --> 01:34:07,199
How'd you figure that?

1765
01:34:07,496 --> 01:34:08,668
I found your ledger.

1766
01:34:09,398 --> 01:34:10,604
You know, the one that you stuck

1767
01:34:10,666 --> 01:34:12,737
in the owner's manual
of your Ferrari.

1768
01:34:12,969 --> 01:34:14,004
Tsk, tsk, tsk.

1769
01:34:14,303 --> 01:34:16,078
I'm guessing you don't
really care about the car.

1770
01:34:16,138 --> 01:34:17,981
You could care less
about 45 million,

1771
01:34:18,074 --> 01:34:20,611
but I bet you want
that ledger back.

1772
01:34:21,243 --> 01:34:22,586
Am I right?

1773
01:34:22,645 --> 01:34:23,817
What do you think you're doing?

1774
01:34:26,382 --> 01:34:28,191
Sacrificing my queen.

1775
01:34:32,755 --> 01:34:35,065
Okay, you and I are gonna
make a deal, Josh.

1776
01:34:35,124 --> 01:34:38,662
A deal that will make you and
your friends very wealthy.

1777
01:34:39,362 --> 01:34:42,070
Do you think that car has value?
Multiply it by 10.

1778
01:34:42,665 --> 01:34:44,008
In cash.

1779
01:34:48,537 --> 01:34:50,380
Dev'Reaux, will you
please remind Mr. Shaw?

1780
01:34:51,907 --> 01:34:55,377
I'm very sorry, Mr. Shaw, but we
don't accept tips at The Tower.

1781
01:34:59,448 --> 01:35:00,791
Checkmate.

1782
01:35:08,691 --> 01:35:10,136
Hello!

1783
01:35:15,798 --> 01:35:18,472
We've got FBI agents and
police all over the city.

1784
01:35:18,534 --> 01:35:20,605
We know about your friend
Slide from Astoria.

1785
01:35:20,970 --> 01:35:22,313
Your little trick
with Lester may have

1786
01:35:22,371 --> 01:35:23,645
gotten the car
out of the building,

1787
01:35:23,739 --> 01:35:26,948
but it's just a matter of
time before we find it.

1788
01:35:28,744 --> 01:35:30,052
Who is this?

1789
01:35:30,112 --> 01:35:31,147
Director Mazin.

1790
01:35:31,380 --> 01:35:33,690
I am Mr. Kovaks' attorney,
Miss lovenko.

1791
01:35:33,783 --> 01:35:36,024
I will be representing all
the defendants in this case.

1792
01:35:37,920 --> 01:35:40,696
And you're licensed to practice
in the state of New York?

1793
01:35:41,190 --> 01:35:43,602
I passed the bar
three days ago.

1794
01:35:48,164 --> 01:35:50,804
I'd like to request the immediate
release of all the defendants.

1795
01:35:52,168 --> 01:35:53,408
On what grounds?

1796
01:35:57,673 --> 01:35:59,346
These are Mr. Shaw's
hand-written notes

1797
01:35:59,408 --> 01:36:01,388
detailing his fraudulent
business practices.

1798
01:36:01,444 --> 01:36:03,390
There are names, dates,
account numbers.

1799
01:36:03,446 --> 01:36:04,948
My guess is you'll find
enough evidence in there

1800
01:36:05,014 --> 01:36:06,322
to put him away
for a very long time.

1801
01:36:06,382 --> 01:36:09,329
But this only happens
if my clients walk.

1802
01:36:10,252 --> 01:36:11,959
You've been a lawyer
for less than a week

1803
01:36:12,054 --> 01:36:14,830
and you're trying to bribe the
United States government?

1804
01:36:15,758 --> 01:36:17,999
Sharks are born swimming, sir.

1805
01:36:25,267 --> 01:36:27,144
I'll let everyone
walk but Kovaks.

1806
01:36:27,636 --> 01:36:31,778
As a first-time offender, he'll
probably get two years for the car.

1807
01:36:32,541 --> 01:36:33,918
Best I can do.

1808
01:36:39,748 --> 01:36:41,591
Nobody else will be charged?

1809
01:36:44,520 --> 01:36:46,591
<i>New evidence
in the Arthur Shaw trial</i>

1810
01:36:46,655 --> 01:36:49,761
<i>has prompted a new plea
from the accused swindler.</i>

1811
01:36:49,825 --> 01:36:52,032
<i>Sources are now
confirming that Mr. Shaw</i>

1812
01:36:52,094 --> 01:36:54,438
<i>will enter
a guilty plea next week.</i>

1813
01:36:59,001 --> 01:37:01,208
Are we gonna do this or what?
Mmm-hmm.

1814
01:37:15,518 --> 01:37:17,020
Hallelujah!

1815
01:37:24,960 --> 01:37:27,463
Welcome to the
penthouse, Mr. Shaw.

1816
01:37:28,430 --> 01:37:30,034
Look who's coming now.

1817
01:37:31,700 --> 01:37:34,408
Wait until I get
a hold of your wrinkled ass.

1818
01:37:34,470 --> 01:37:36,416
He looks good!

1819
01:37:46,282 --> 01:37:47,852
Are you Rose Demato?
Yes.

1820
01:37:47,917 --> 01:37:49,362
Sign right here, please.

1821
01:37:51,487 --> 01:37:52,659
All right, thanks.

1822
01:38:16,712 --> 01:38:18,282
It's a gold wheel!